I have posted in the community about this and having not got any response in month have decided it's not possible... but it should be! basicly just the ability to turn off all outgoing email for a project. below is my community post for more context.



We have setup the Service Desk and so far things are great but we created a project called systems to receive email from appliances (phone systems, NAS devices, Backup systems etc.). The idea is these alerts or notices can then be sent to service staff instead of one member having to forward the emails just to get lost in someones inbox.
however as the appliances do not have incoming email and often don't even have real addresses (some send from servername@local.local) we would like to setup the project to never send emails (setup account, new issue, comments, resolved) to the "customers" instead just to accept the email and create an event. I tried changing notifications to none but it is still sending some. is there anyway at all to disable these?

